Splunk4Rookies (SA-S4R) — local/ workshop guide
=================================================

Splunk apps use local/ for instance-specific overrides (nav, dashboards, field
extractions, saved searches). local/ wins at runtime over default/.

In this repo, everything under SA-S4R/local/ is gitignored except this README.
Create workshop files on your bind-mounted app path (or in Splunk Web — saves
land under local/ automatically). Never customize default/ for workshop assets.

After editing files under local/, run: make restart

Layout spec (panels, SPL, acceptance): docs/S4R-DASHBOARD.md
Canonical SPL: docs/S4R-SPL-CATALOG.md
Full app notes: docs/SA-S4R-APP.md

Expected local/ layout (workshop)
---------------------------------

  local/
  ├── README                 (this file — tracked in git)
  ├── props.conf             (Lab 4 — platform extraction)
  ├── data/ui/nav/local.xml  (Buttercup nav tab)
  ├── data/ui/views/         (Dashboard Studio export — build in Labs 3–7)
  └── metadata/local.meta    (permissions for the dashboard view)

Lab 4 — platform field extraction (local/props.conf)
----------------------------------------------------

Add to local/props.conf (not default/props.conf):

  [access_combined]
  EXTRACT-platform = \((?<platform>Linux; Android [0-9.]+|Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X [0-9_]+|Windows|iPhone; CPU iPhone OS [0-9_]+)

Saved dashboard panels can use platform after this. Splunk MCP / agents must
still use the inline rex in docs/S4R-SPL-CATALOG.md (§ Platform prefix).

Workshop nav tab (local/data/ui/nav/local.xml)
----------------------------------------------

  <nav search_view="search" color="#791CF8">
    <view name="buttercup_enterprises_dashboard" />
  </nav>

Dashboard permissions (local/metadata/local.meta)
-------------------------------------------------

  [views/buttercup_enterprises_dashboard]
  access = read : [ admin, sc_admin, power, user ], write : [ admin, sc_admin ]
  export = none

Dashboard Studio view (Labs 3–7)
--------------------------------

Build the Buttercup Enterprises dashboard in Splunk Web (Dashboard Studio,
Absolute layout). Save under local/data/ui/views/ — do not save to default/.

Panel order, visualizations, background image, and checklist:
  docs/S4R-DASHBOARD.md

Background asset (already in default/ static):
  /static/app/SA-S4R/Buttercup_Background.jpg

Packaging
---------

SA-S4R.spl (package-s4r.yml) excludes local/ — workshop UI is not shipped in
the published app bundle. PoC baseline stays in default/.
